The Beijing Chinese Orchestra performs in Beijing on Saturday. Photo: Courtesy of Huang XinziThe Beijing Chinese Orchestra held a free open day in the capital on Saturday. Nearly 400 fans of Chinese folk music took part in the event, which allowed them to interact with musicians from the orchestra. A series of performances were also held that day by the orchestra, which mainly focuses on Chinese folk music and instruments. The orchestra also announced its plans for three upcoming shows. In the following weeks, the orchestra will perform local songs in the dialect of northern Shaanxi Province with singer Du Pengpeng, a Heroes are Cultivated from Childhood concert and a National Ceremonial Music concert. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun